📌 One-to-One Mapping (JPA / Hibernate)
🔹 Concept
A One-to-One relationship means:
One entity is associated with exactly one instance of another entity.
Example:
User ↔ Profile
Person ↔ Passport
👉 Each record in Table A maps to one and only one record in Table B.

🔹 Types of One-to-One Mapping
1. Unidirectional
Only one entity knows about the relationship.
👉 Example:
User → Profile
(Profile does NOT know User)


2. Bidirectional
Both entities reference each other.
👉 Example:
User ↔ Profile


🔹 Approaches to Implement
✅ 1. Using Foreign Key (Most Common)
One table contains a foreign key of the other.

✅ 2. Using Shared Primary Key
Both tables share the same primary key.

🔹 Approach 1: Foreign Key Mapping
🧩 Example (Unidirectional)
Entity 1: User
@Entity
public class User {

    @Id
    @GeneratedValue
    private Long id;

    private String name;

    @OneToOne
    @JoinColumn(name = "profile_id") // FK column
    private Profile profile;
}


Entity 2: Profile
@Entity
public class Profile {

    @Id
    @GeneratedValue
    private Long id;

    private String bio;
}


