🔹 Approach 2: Shared Primary Key
📌 When to Use
When both entities are tightly coupled (e.g., User ↔ Profile)

Example
User
@Entity
public class User {

    @Id
    @GeneratedValue
    private Long id;

    private String name;

    @OneToOne(mappedBy = "user", cascade = CascadeType.ALL)
    private Profile profile;
}


Profile
@Entity
public class Profile {

    @Id
    private Long id;

    private String bio;

    @OneToOne
    @MapsId
    @JoinColumn(name = "id")
    private User user;
}


