🔹 Best Practices
Prefer foreign key mapping for flexibility.
Use bidirectional mapping only when needed.
Avoid unnecessary EAGER loading.
Use cascade carefully (especially REMOVE).
Always define owning side correctly.

🔹 Common Mistakes
❌ Forgetting mappedBy in bidirectional mapping
❌ Infinite recursion in JSON (use @JsonIgnore)
❌ Using EAGER unnecessarily
❌ Not handling cascade properly

🔹 Real-World Examples
User ↔ Profile
Person ↔ Passport
Order ↔ Invoice

🔹 Learnings / Interview Tips
Default fetch type for @OneToOne = EAGER
Owner side = entity with @JoinColumn
mappedBy = inverse side (no DB column)
Shared PK uses @MapsId
One-to-One can be replaced with One-to-Many (rare cases for flexibility)

