| student_id | course_id  |
+------------+------------+


📌 Best Practices ✅
Prefer bidirectional only if needed
Use Set instead of List (avoid duplicates)
Avoid CascadeType.REMOVE
Use explicit join table name
Keep fetch LAZY

📌 Common Mistakes ❌
Forgetting mappedBy
Using two owners ❌
Not maintaining both sides
Using EAGER (performance issue)

📌 Advanced Insight ⭐
👉 In real projects, Many-to-Many is often converted to two One-to-Many
Why?
Because join table may need extra fields like:
enrollmentDate
status

Example:
Student → Enrollment ← Course

👉 Enrollment becomes a separate entity

📌 Real-World Examples
Student ↔ Course
User ↔ Role
Actor ↔ Movie

📌 Interview Learnings 🚀
Requires join table
No direct FK in main tables
Owner controls join table
Avoid ManyToMany in complex systems
Prefer intermediate entity

🔹 One-Line Answer 🎯
Many-to-Many mapping represents a relationship where multiple entities are associated with multiple others and is implemented using a join table containing foreign keys of both entities.

